Toast pinenuts in 350 degree F. oven for 5-7 minutes. Cool. Slice top and bottom off each tomato and save for another use or discard. Cut each tomato into three slices. Transfer to plates. In a bowl, combine peppers, olives, basil and parsley; toss with 1/4 cup Marzetti Light Balsamic Dressing. Layer each tomato with a Mozzarella slice. Evenly distribute mixture in between each layer of tomato and on top. Sprinkle pinenuts and drizzle with remaining Marzetti Light Balsamic Dressing. Serve with pita chips.